name: B. Kevin and Permutation
input: InputEach test consists of multiple test cases. The first line contains the number of test cases $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \le t \le 10^3$$$).The only line of each test case contains two integers $$$ n $$$ and $$$ k $$$ ($$$ 1\le k\le n\le 10^5 $$$).It is guaranteed that the sum of $$$ n $$$ over all test cases doesn't exceed $$$ 10^5 $$$.
output: OutputFor each test case, output $$$ n $$$ integers on a single line — the permutation $$$ p $$$ you constructed.If there are multiple answers, you can print any of them.
